# Confluence Mirror Demo - Environment Variables
#
# Choose ONE authentication method:
#
# Option 1: OAuth2 Authentication (Recommended for service accounts)
# =====================================================================
# OAuth2 uses service accounts with Client Credentials Flow (2LO).
# Only Client ID and Client Secret are required - Cloud ID is auto-detected.
#
# To set up OAuth2:
# 1. Go to https://admin.atlassian.com
# 2. Navigate to Directory > Service accounts
# 3. Create or select a service account
# 4. Click "Create credentials" > "OAuth 2.0"
# 5. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret below

CONFLUENCE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=your_oauth_client_id
CONFLUENCE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=your_oauth_client_secret

# Option 2: Basic Authentication (Legacy)
# ========================================
# Uses email + API key for authentication.
# To use Basic Auth, comment out the OAuth2 variables above and uncomment below:
#
# CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL=https://your-domain.atlassian.net
# CONFLUENCE_EMAIL=your.email@example.com
# CONFLUENCE_API_KEY=your_confluence_api_key